      <p>
        The most effective negotiators can adapt their style based on the situation and the other party's approach. Consider these general principles for adapting to different contexts:
      </p>
      
      <div class="adaptation-principles">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>High stakes negotiations:</strong> Invest time in collaboration, especially when creativity and relationship are important</li>
          <li><strong>Time pressure:</strong> Compromising may be more efficient when a quick resolution is needed</li>
          <li><strong>Power imbalance:</strong> When you have less power, preparation and objective standards become even more crucial</li>
          <li><strong>Cultural differences:</strong> Be aware that negotiation styles vary across cultures; adapt accordingly</li>
          <li><strong>Emotional situations:</strong> Consider temporary avoidance to allow emotions to cool before re-engaging</li>
        </ul>
